[30;1m936 | [0m[35m## Bundling Asset Code[0m
[30;1m937 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m938 | [0m[35mWhen using `lambda.Code.fromAsset(path)` it is possible to bundle the code by running a[0m
[30;1m939 | [0m[35mcommand in a Docker container. The asset path will be mounted at `/asset-input`. The[0m
[30;1m940 | [0m[35mDocker container is responsible for putting content at `/asset-output`. The content at[0m
[30;1m941 | [0m[35m`/asset-output` will be zipped and used as Lambda code.[0m
[30;1m942 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m943 | [0m[35mExample with Python:[0m

[30;1m818 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m850 | [0m[35m## Bundling Asset Code[0m
[30;1m851 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m852 | [0m[35mWhen using `lambda.Code.fromAsset(path)` it is possible to bundle the code by running a[0m
[30;1m853 | [0m[35mcommand in a Docker container. The asset path will be mounted at `/asset-input`. The[0m
[30;1m854 | [0m[35mDocker container is responsible for putting content at `/asset-output`. The content at[0m
[30;1m855 | [0m[35m`/asset-output` will be zipped and used as Lambda code.[0m
